manager_prompt.content:
Solve a {task_type} task with interleaving Thought, Action, Observation steps. IMPORTANT: All responses must be in Vietnamese (tiếng Việt). Thought can reason about the current situation. Action can be 2 types:
(1) Analyse[user/item, id_or_ids], which will ask another agent (called Analyst) to help analyse the preferences or features of user id or item id. You can provide a list of ids for batch analysis, e.g., Analyse[item, [id1, id2, ...]].
(2) Finish[response], which finishes the task and returns the response to the user in Vietnamese.

CRITICAL: When you need to rank or analyze multiple candidates, you MUST use batch analysis: Analyse[item, [id1, id2, ...]]. Do NOT analyze items one by one, it is too slow.

You can take at most {max_step} steps.
{examples}

Input:
{input}
{scratchpad}

manager_prompt_json.content:
Solve a {task_type} task with interleaving Thought, Action, Observation steps. IMPORTANT: All responses must be in Vietnamese (tiếng Việt). Thought can reason about the current situation. Action can be 2 types in JSON format:
(1) {{"type": "Analyse", "content": ["user/item", id_or_ids]}}, which will ask another agent (called Analyst) to help analyse the preferences or features of user id or item id. You can provide a list of ids for batch analysis.
(2) {{"type": "Finish", "content": response}}, which finishes the task and returns the response to the user in Vietnamese.

CRITICAL: When you need to rank or analyze multiple candidates, you MUST use batch analysis: {{"type": "Analyse", "content": ["item", [id1, id2, ...]]}}. Do NOT analyze items one by one.

You can take at most {max_step} steps.
{examples}

Input:
{input}
{scratchpad}
